1.title: Jackee Harry/Traci Lords
1.plot: In the season premiere, when it's time for the rules to change, Jackée Harry and Traci Lords are both ready to shake things up and get their new families out of their usual routine.

2.title: Verne Troyer/Hines Ward
2.plot: Verne Troyer's girlfriend leaves her quaint home and laid-back lifestyle in Los Angeles and heads to Atlanta, to switch places with Hines Ward's wife, who's used to a huge house and structured environment.

3.title: Jeremy London/David & Jackie Siegel
3.plot: Juliet Reeves London, the wife of 90s heartthrob Jeremy London, swaps lives with Jaqueline Siegel, the self-proclaimed "Queen of Versailles", wife of David Siegel.

4.title: Tami Roman/Kerri Walsh-Jennings
4.plot: Olympic Gold Medalist Kerri Walsh Jennings swaps her healthy eating and exercise lifestyle for takeout dinners and the city nightlife of Tami Roman.

5.title: Charo/Jill Whelan
5.plot: It's a "Love Boat" reunion, when Charo and Jill Whelan swap lives for a week. Both Charo and Jill are excited for their upcoming adventure. Having worked together on The Love Boat (1977), they recognize their "new families" right away. But, will Charo's "all showbiz, all the time" mentality be a match for Jill's "leave Hollywood at the door" household?

6.title: Vince Neil/Gunnar Nelson
6.plot: Vince Neil's girlfriend leaves her big home, flashy cars and late-night parties in Las Vegas and swaps places with Gunnar Nelson's wife, who lives a quiet, family-focused life in Nashville.

7.title: Margaret Cho/Holly Robinson-Peete
7.plot: Margaret Cho is a stand-up comedienne, with numerous successful comedy specials, who loves to push the envelope with her racy jokes. Holly Robinson Peete is an actress best-known for roles on 21 Jump Street (1987) and Hangin' with Mr. Cooper (1992). When it's time for the swap, both Margaret and Holly meet their new families and know they are in for an adventure.

8.title: Cloris Leachman/Pia Zadora
8.plot: Nature-loving Cloris Leachman trade lives with reclusive actress Pia Zadora.

9.title: Sean Lowe/Jason Mesnick
9.plot: Sean Lowe's wife, Catherine Lowe, trades places with Molly Malaney, Jason Mesnick's wife.

10.title: George Hamilton & Alana Stewart/Angela 'Big Ang' Raiola
10.plot: Alana Stewart leaves behind quiet, yoga-filled days w/ex-husband George Hamilton in Beverly Hills, and swaps places w/Angela Raiola (Big Ang), who prepares big Italian meals for her family in Staten Island, N.Y.

11.title: Tommy Davidson/Corey Feldman
11.plot: Tommy Davidson's fiancée leaves behind her quiet, family-focused life and swap places with Corey Feldman's girlfriend, who's used to wearing pajamas and lingerie all day and eating a diet of just fruit.

12.title: CeCe Peniston/Kellie Williams
12.plot: Actress Kellie Shanygne Williams trade lives with singer Ce Ce Peniston for a week.

13.title: Robert Carradine/Terrell Owens
13.plot: Robert Carradine leaves behind his secluded, off-the-grid island life with his family and swaps places with Terrell Owens, who lives in a sprawling Los Angeles home and devotes much of his time to working out.

1.title: Tracey Gold/Carnie Wilson
1.plot: Best known for her role as Carol Seaver in the legendary comedy series "Growing Pains," Tracey Gold runs a tight ship in her home. She and her husband, Roby Marshall, are inseparable and keep strict daily schedules for their four boys -- Sage (14), Bailey (12), Aiden (7) and Dylan (3). Each day, Gold makes sure the family eats their meals together, and from sunrise to sunset she and Roby are diligently managing their household by cooking, cleaning, doing laundry and running errands. Gold swaps lives with Carnie Wilson, a member of the successful music group Wilson ...

2.title: Gary Busey/Ted Haggard
2.plot: Gary, Steffanie and their 19-month old son, Luke, live in their Hollywood Hills home. Gary, born into Christianity and Steffanie, born into Judaism, have chosen to live spiritually and believe in reincarnation. They claim to be soul mates, married in spirit, and believe they are currently spending their 32nd lifetime together. When Gary is not working, he spends his time transcribing his visions from his experiences and his life now. Steffanie is a hands-on mother who has recently returned to her career as a hypnotherapist and healer. Steffanie travels to the Haggard ...

3.title: Flavor Flav/Dee Snider
3.plot: Flavor Flav's and Dee Snider's wives, trade places.

4.title: Niecy Nash/Tina Yothers
4.plot: City-girl Niecy and country girl Tina, swap lives.

5.title: Mick 'Mankind' Foley/Antonio Sabato Jr.
5.plot: The time spent apart ends up being too much for one couple to handle.

1.title: Kate Gosselin/Kendra Wilkinson
1.plot: Reality-TV stars Kate Gosselin and Kendra Wilkinson switch places.

2.title: Coolio/Mark McGrath
2.plot: Rapper Coolio's girlfriend switches places with singer Mark McGrath's wife, Carin Kingsland McGrath.

3.title: Gilbert Gottfried/Alan Thicke
3.plot: Alan Thicke's wife, Tanya Callau, trades places with Gilbert Gottfried's wife, Dara Kravitz.

4.title: Bristol & Willow Palin/Melissa & Joan Rivers
4.plot: Bristol and Willow Palin, daughters of former Alaska Gov. Sarah Palin, trade lives with one of TV's most popular mother-daughter duos, Joan and Melissa Rivers.

5.title: Ric Flair/'Rowdy' Roddy Piper
5.plot: The significant others of two former professional wrestlers.

6.title: Nia Peeples/Tiffany
6.plot: Actress Nia Peeples and former pop star Tiffany trade lives for a week.

7.title: Andy Dick/Lorenzo Lamas
7.plot: The former flame of Andy Dick and the wife of Lorenzo Lamas swap lives.

8.title: Downtown Julie Brown/Lisa Leslie
8.plot: "Downtown" Julie Brown and Lisa Leslie swap lives for one week.

9.title: Gerardo/Sisqó
9.plot: The wife and the girlfriend of the '90s' biggest musical artists swap.

1.title: Daniel Baldwin/Jermaine Jackson
1.plot: In the season debut, actor Daniel Baldwin's former girlfriend, Isabella Hofmann, lives in the Hollywood Hills with their autistic son Atticus. After struggling for a decade with drug addiction, Daniel is now sober and working on rebuilding his relationship with both Isabella and Atticus. Meanwhile, in Calabasas, CA, music legend Jermaine Jackson and his wife, Halima, live a privileged life with their prized show dog, Fiji.

2.title: Robin Leach/Eric Roberts
2.plot: Robin Leach is best known as the host of the long-running television series "Lifestyles of the Rich and Famous." Today, Robin keeps a lavish lifestyle in Las Vegas, NV complete with his "Lifelong Heartstring" Joan Severance. Robin and Joan enjoy spending almost every evening out on The Strip. Meanwhile, in Los Angeles, CA, Eric Roberts and his wife Eliza live a quiet life, complete with a squirrel sanctuary in the backyard. Eliza, an actress in her own right, is not only Eric's partner in life, but partner in work as Eric's manager and radio show co-host. When it's ...

3.title: Tichina Arnold/Kelly Packard
3.plot: Actress Tichina Arnold ("Martin") lives in New York City with her husband, basketball coach Rico, and their daughter Alijah. Their relaxed parenting approach and end-of-day rituals is the complete opposite of television actress Kelly Packard ("Baywatch"). Today, Kelly lives in Newhall, CA with her husband, ER trauma doctor, Darrin, and their four children. The family is Mormon and abstains from alcohol, tobacco products, and even caffeine. From getting the kids up and out the door for school, and caring for the animals, to the cooking and cleaning, Kelly rarely has a ...

4.title: Laila Ali/Angie Stone
4.plot: Former professional boxer Laila Ali trades lives with singer-songwriter Angie Stone.

5.title: Angie Everhart/Pat & Gina Neely
5.plot: Supermodel and actress Angie Everhart lives in Los Angeles, CA with her boyfriend, Carl, her son Kayden, and Carl's daughter Joann. When it comes to caring for the children, Angie and Carl split duties. Food Network stars and best-selling authors Pat and Gina Neely live in Memphis, TN. They have been married almost 20 years. As a couple that lives and works together, Pat and Gina spend a lot of time together. The biggest difference between these two households is their eating habits--one cooks and the other relies on pre-packaged meals.

6.title: Larry Birkhead/Helio Castroneves
6.plot: The former boyfriend of Anna Nicole Smith, Larry Birkhead, who resides in Louisville, Kentucky with his daughter, DannieLynn, his sister, and her two children, swaps places with three-time Indianapolis 500 and "Dancing with the Stars" champion Helio Castroneves, who lives in Ft. Lauderdale, Florida with his girlfriend and daughter.

7.title: David Justice/Dweezil Zappa
7.plot: Former major league baseball star David Justice and Grammy-award winning musical artist Dweezil Zappa swap lives with their wives! It's a shock to both families this week due to David's luxurious lifestyle in San Diego in contrast with Dweezil's simplistic and eco-friendly household in Los Angeles.

8.title: Amanda Beard/Heidi & Spencer Pratt
8.plot: Four-time Olympic swimmer Amanda Beard swaps places with Heidi Pratt of "The Hills" fame. Amanda moves down into Spencer and Heidi's Santa Barbara beach house, far from her secluded cottage in Seattle. It's not long before she feels uncomfortable, as Spencer whisks her off to a nightclub for a paparazzi-filled evening. Meanwhile, Heidi takes on motherhood as she learns what it takes to be a mom of two.

9.title: Judy Gold/Penn Jillette
9.plot: Comedian Judy Gold lives in a cramped Manhattan apartment with her fiancee Elisa and two sons. The family likes to stay active play competitive sports together. Judy and her family are Jewish, and religion plays an important role in their lives. Meanwhile, magician Penn Jillette lives in Las Vegas, NV with his wife Emily and their two children. The family resides on a secluded and expansive piece of land. His kids don't like to participate in sports and prefer to spend time inside doing educational activities. Penn and his wife are atheists and do not expose their ...

10.title: Joe Piscopo/Barry Williams
10.plot: Comedian Joe Piscopo lives just outside New York in an expansive home with two of his children. "Brady Bunch" star Barry Williams, famous for playing Greg Brady, lives in Branson, Missouri with his right-hand woman Marie and his son Brandon. When Marie swaps places with Joe's personal assistant, Jessica, she has a rough time understanding their relationship.

11.title: Jenna von Oy/Jill Zarin
11.plot: "Blossom" actress Jenna von Oy lives in Nashville, TN with her husband Brad and daughter Gray. Expecting their second daughter, Brad and Jenna are hands-on parents who do everything together, including all of the household chores. Jill Zarin is an original cast member of Bravo's "The Real Housewives of New York City." Zarin lives in the lap of luxury with her husband Bobby, daughter Ally, and dog Ginger in The Hamptons. Zarin employs a staff that handles all of the cooking, cleaning and home maintenance needs. The Zarin family loves to entertain, enjoy spoiling the ...

12.title: Tyler Christopher/Ronn Moss
12.plot: "General Hospital" star Tyler Christopher lives in Malibu, CA with his wife Brienne and their son Greysun. The outdoorsy actor has a hands-on approach in raising his picky-eater son, especially when trying to eat healthy. Meanwhile, former "The Bold and The Beautiful" star Ronn Moss is an accomplished musician living outside Hollywood, CA with his wife Devin. The couple loves to entertainment in their lavish home.

13.title: Plaxico Burress/DJ Paul
13.plot: Rapper DJ Paul is one half of the rap duo Three 6 Mafia. DJ Paul lives in Las Vegas with his fiancee Majda and son Nautica. He loves to entertain and has family and friends over regularly for backyard barbecues. DJ Paul spends a lot of time in the studio recording where Majda hangs out with his crew. Former NFL wide receiver Plaxico Burress lives in New Jersey with his wife Tiffany and their two children. Plaxico likes to spend his free time downstairs in his "man cave" alone. Tiffany is responsible for the running of the household. She also takes the lead in terms of...

imdb.plot outline: In each episode, two mothers with very different types of households swap lifestyles and children in a week-long challenge. In the first part of the swap, each mom moves into the others home and adopts their new celebrity family's lifestyle, no matter how different it may be. They agree to follow a manual written by the departing mother that sets out the rules of their new household - how they parent, manage their social life, do house work, unwind and more. In the second half of the week, everything changes. The new moms take charge. They introduce their own set of rules and get to run the new household their way. It's a radical shock to both celebrity families. The results are explosive, enlightening, emotional and often very funny. At the end of the show, the two celebrity couples meet for the first time.
